The Supreme Court was originally established with just one chief justice and seven other judges, but the number has grown over time due to various amendments to the Constitution of India and other factors. Today, the Supreme Court plays a vital role in the Indian judicial system, hearing appeals from lower courts and providing guidance on legal issues that are of national importance.
